# Accessibility

## Interactive Components

- Always set `accessibilityRole` and `accessibilityLabel`.

```tsx
<Button accessibilityLabel="Save changes" accessibilityRole="button" />
```

## Buttons

- Prefer DS `Button`.
- If using `Pressable`, wire state + labels manually.

```tsx
<Pressable
  accessibilityRole="button"
  accessibilityLabel="Submit"
  onPress={submit}
/>
```

## Inputs

- Inputs must have labels and error text for screen readers.

```tsx
<Input label="Email" error="Invalid email" />
```

## Color Contrast

- Do not rely on color alone to indicate state.
- Always include icons, text, or other cues.
